Package: rvtable
Type: Package
Title: Random Variable Data Tables
Version: 0.3.0
Date: 2017-08-11
Author: Matthew Leonwicz [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Matthew Leonawicz <mfleonawicz@alaska.edu>
Authors@R: person("Matthew", "Leonawicz", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "mfleonawicz@alaska.edu")
URL: https://github.com/leonawicz/rvtable
BugReports: https://github.com/leonawicz/rvtable/issues
Description: Store distributions of random variables in long format data tables
    with the 'rvtable' class. The package provides a simplified and consistent
    interface for managing and manipulating random variables. Random variables can
    be conditioned on levels of categorical variables stored in a table's
    ID columns. Functions provide the ability to condition on/subset, marginalize/
    integrate over, and draw random samples from an rvtable. Emphasis is on
    continuous probability density functions empirically estimated from large samples.
